-- Koor, China National Chemicals May Take Israel's Makhteshim-Agan Private
-- B y   D a v i d   W a i n e r
-- 2010-10-11T09:51:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/koor-china-national-chemicals-may-take-israel-s-makhteshim-agan-private.html
 Koor Industries Ltd. said it
reached an “initial understanding” with China National
Chemical Corporation to take Makhteshim-Agan Industries Ltd.
private according to a statement to the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange.
Under the terms being discussed, Koor would sell a 17 percent
stake in Makhteshim and ChemChina would acquire the rest of the
stake from the public in a deal which would value Makhteshim at
$2.72 billion. Koor would keep a 30 percent stake in Makhteshim,
while ChemChina would hold a 70 percent stake, according to the
terms of the deal under discussion, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
